EndSARS campaigner and popular comedian, Debo Adedayo, Mr Macaroni, has said he does not hate against any government official.  Although he didn’t mention any name, Mr Macaroni stated that he is just interested in ensuring every Nigerian attains better life. He said: “I was at an event day before yesterday, a top government worker walks up to me and asks why I hate “someone” ~ I can’t mention name. “I have no hate whatsoever in my heart. “I just want a better life for every Nigerian. “I don’t hate anyone. We all can do better.”   Source Popular Nigerian comedian, Mr Macaroni has given his two cents after Nigerians called out Governor Nyesom Wike for giving Burna Boy a land, money to build and promising to give all artists who performed at his homecoming concert N10m each last weekend while teachers were reportedly owed wages. Recall that… In "Entertainment" Popular Nigerian online skit maker, Mr Macaroni, has taken to his verified Twitter account to reveal the ordeal he faced when he was arrested by the Police during one of the #EndSARS protests. Following the October 20, 2020 shootings at the Lekki Tollgate, many people kicked against the recommendation for… In "Entertainment" Debo Adedayo, the social media comedian, actor and activist, aka Mr Macaroni, has said that his activism sometimes comes at a cost. According to him, after protesting at the Lekki tollgate some months ago, a brand cancelled the deal they had with him. He told Sunday Scoop, “On the day… In "Entertainment"